Step 1: Calculate the Quick Ratio.
• Quick assets include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable. Inventory is not included.
• From the balance sheet (End_amount values):
  Cash on Hand = 2,103,508.95
  Bank Deposits = 4,714,000.00
  Interest Receivable = 15,414.09
  Accounts Receivable = 3,149,338.94
  Sum of quick assets = 2,103,508.95 + 4,714,000.00 + 15,414.09 + 3,149,338.94 = 9,982,261.98
• Total Current Liabilities = 499,821.72
• Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 9,982,261.98 / 499,821.72 ≈ 19.96

Step 2: Calculate the Net Profit Margin.
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement:
  Net Profit = 1,390,936.99
  Total Revenue = 3,956,433.90
• Net Profit Margin = (1,390,936.99 / 3,956,433.90) × 100% ≈ 35.17%

Thus, the solution is:
